    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Trea Turner** (73.57) and **Christian Yelich** (72.61) anchoring the lineup as our most reliable offensive drivers. **Trea Turner** benefits from a high-leadoff position and a favorable BvP trend against Gallen, while **Christian Yelich** faces a prime dynamic platoon advantage against Littell, driving his score deep into the strong tier. Both **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82) and **Colt Keith** (67.49) also offer significant upside; **Colt Keith** specifically benefits from an elite combination of a favorable park and a slow opposing delivery that should invite aggressive baserunning opportunities, a crucial factor for our SB-weighted roster strategy.\n\nManaging our depth remains a precise exercise, evidenced by the exclusion of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (55.67). While he displayed potential against Chandler, the optimizer ultimately favored the efficiency of **Jerar Encarnacion** (56.19) due to a massive 16% park factor bump that outweighed the marginal gains of **Pete Crow-Armstrong**\u2019s platoon edge. Elsewhere, we are cautious with **Yordan Alvarez** (53.98); while his raw talent remains elite, a sub-3.00 xERA matchup against Gilbert suppresses his daily floor, making him a start based on quality rather than a ceiling-chaser today. Conversely, **Josh Smith** (62.01) represents a high-leverage start, as he faces a favorable 5.52 xERA from Sasaki, allowing him to outperform several of our bench options despite a lower spot in the batting order. We continue to monitor the status of **Hyeseong Kim**, **Carson Benge**, **Victor Scott II**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, and **Luis Pena** as potential rotation pivots, but for today, the current configuration offers the most robust path to balancing our 5x5 categories.",
